{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review PASS (0 blocking, 4 advisory). Remediation: (1 critical) cross-phase data-flow entanglement — reconcile_once threads many locals (snapshot, binding_store, client, pass_id, mutation lists, manifest, alert state) across load->diff->apply->persist. Design: extract phase helpers that take/return EXPLICIT params (or a small in-file context) rather than relying on closure state, so each phase is independently testable; verify byte-for-byte behavior via the existing idempotency + corrupt-snapshot tests. (minor x3) ACs 'materially shorter'/'max nesting drops' lack thresholds — will report concrete before/after LOC + nesting; extracting 5 helpers at once is risky — will extract incrementally and run the reconcile suite after each. Branching off the unfed-liner-arson branch (both touch reconcile.py) to avoid a merge conflict."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782690644552897001,"uuid":"b9e80289-a43d-4006-8b0b-82dc9cbeb4ef"}